        <h2 class="centered-title">SEA TRADING SYSTEM</h2>
        <div class="hero-image"></div>
        <div class="product-grid">
            <div class="product">
                <h3>Overview of The Sea Trading System</h3>
                <p>The Sea Trading System, developed by Russ Horn, is a versatile Forex trading strategy designed for use across various timeframes and currency pairs, especially major pairs like EUR/USD and GBP/USD. The system is named for its reliance on indicators that trigger signals when they fall below or rise above their middle levels, resembling a sea level.</p>

                <h3>System Components & Indicators</h3>
                <ul>
                    <li><strong>Bollinger Bands (20,3)</strong></li>
                    <li><strong>3-period Exponential Moving Average (EMA)</strong></li>
                    <li><strong>MACD (6,17,1)</strong></li>
                    <li><strong>14-period Relative Strength Index (RSI)</strong></li>
                </ul>

                <h3>Chart Setup</h3>
                <ul>
                    <li><strong>Bollinger Bands (20,3):</strong> Apply with a 20-period, 3 standard deviations, on the closing prices.</li>
                    <li><strong>3-period EMA:</strong> Apply with a 3-period on the closing prices.</li>
                    <li><strong>MACD (6,17,1):</strong> Set with a Fast EMA of 6, Slow EMA of 17, and MACD SMA of 1.</li>
                    <li><strong>14-period RSI:</strong> Apply with a period of 14 and a level set at 50.</li>
                </ul>

                <h3>Buy Rules</h3>
                <ul>
                    <li>3-period EMA crosses above the Middle Bollinger Band.</li>
                    <li>MACD crosses above the 0 level.</li>
                    <li>14-period RSI crosses above the 50 level.</li>
                    <li>Place a buy order when all conditions are met.</li>
                    <li><strong>Stop Loss:</strong> A few pips below the nearest swing low or the Lower Bollinger Band, whichever is closer.</li>
                    <li><strong>Take Profit:</strong> At the Upper Bollinger Band or a fixed target, depending on the timeframe:
                        <ul>
                            <li><strong>M1:</strong> 3-5 pips</li>
                            <li><strong>M5:</strong> 5-10 pips</li>
                            <li><strong>M15:</strong> 15-20 pips</li>
                            <li><strong>M30:</strong> 25-30 pips</li>
                            <li><strong>H1:</strong> 40-60 pips</li>
                            <li><strong>H4:</strong> 80-100 pips</li>
                            <li><strong>D1:</strong> 150-200 pips</li>
                        </ul>
                    </li>
                </ul>

                <h3>Sell Rules</h3>
                <ul>
                    <li>3-period EMA crosses below the Middle Bollinger Band.</li>
                    <li>MACD falls below the 0 level.</li>
                    <li>14-period RSI moves below the 50 level.</li>
                    <li>Place a sell order when all conditions are met.</li>
                    <li><strong>Stop Loss:</strong> A few pips above the nearest swing high or the Upper Bollinger Band, whichever is closer.</li>
                    <li><strong>Take Profit:</strong> At the Lower Bollinger Band or a fixed target, depending on the timeframe.</li>
                </ul>

                <h3>Example Trades</h3>
                <h4>Long Trade Example</h4>
                <ul>
                    <li><strong>Chart:</strong> GBP/JPY H4</li>
                    <li><strong>Entry:</strong> When RSI crossed above 50, MACD above 0, and 3 EMA above Middle Bollinger Band.</li>
                    <li><strong>Buy Order:</strong> At 126.283</li>
                    <li><strong>Stop Loss:</strong> 80 pips below the entry, at 125.483</li>
                    <li><strong>Take Profit:</strong> 100 pips, at 127.283</li>
                </ul>

                <h4>Short Trade Example</h4>
                <ul>
                    <li><strong>Chart:</strong> EUR/USD H1</li>
                    <li><strong>Entry:</strong> When RSI crossed below 50, 3 EMA below Middle Bollinger Band, and MACD below 0.</li>
                    <li><strong>Sell Order:</strong> At 1.30512</li>
                    <li><strong>Stop Loss:</strong> 15 pips above the entry, at 1.30662</li>
                    <li><strong>Take Profit:</strong> 40 pips, at 1.30112</li>
                </ul>

